• Participate in and contribute to sector technical working groups, meetings and workshops with government, international development partner and further relevant stakeholders;
• Liaise and coordinate with government line ministries, international development partners and other stakeholders working in the same sectors;
• Coordinate with other German development institutions in providing project and sector information.
• Represent our bank'Office during official events, such as inaugurations, presentations.

C) Logistical Support

• Prepare and accompany project team missions during their visits to Cambodia for project appraisals, annual reviews and evaluations. This includes support in organizing and coordinating working agendas and appointments, project mission schedules and fixing administrative and logistical arrangements of official travel, meetings, workshops, etc. It also includes oral and written translations to missions if required.

 + Requirement : 

• Higher university degree (equal to MA) preferably in economics or social sciences, health studies or development and engineering studies (incl. agriculture/rural development) or other related subjects;
• Working experience of at least 3 years in project coordination/project management, in governmental institutions, bi- and multilateral organisations, the private sector or with NGOs;
• In-depth understanding of development issues in Cambodia as well as good knowledge and overview of government policies and strategies as well as government procedure;
• Good analytical and communication skills in Khmer and English (spoken and written). Knowledge of German language will be a plus;

+ VACANCY NOTICE

• Good working knowledge of modern telecommunication, computer literacy and familiarity with standard office software packages;
• Ability and willingness to work in a small team and in close cooperation with the colleagues of bank'headquarter in Frankfurt;
• Ability and willingness to frequently accompany missions from the headquarters in Frankfurt to the field and limited travelling abroad.
• Knowledge or work experience in one or more of bank’s local areas in the fields of rural development and infrastructure, health, financial sector or in the field of natural resource management would be a strong asset.

